Other Changes
Allow Only Trusted Cross-Org Redirections (Release Update)
Adopt Updated Content Security Policy (CSP) Directives (Release Update)
Review and Resolve Blocked External Redirections
IdeaExchange Delivered: Limit Who Receives Notifications About Certificate Expiration
Control Which HTTP Status Codes Refresh Access Tokens for Named Credentials
Confirm Access to External Systems When Named Credentials Use the OAuth 2.0 Browser Flow
Create 3072-Bit Sized Certificates
Audit More Changes to Salesforce Sites and Visualforce Sites
Enjoy Faster Load Times for Cached Salesforce Site Pages
The BrowserId_sec Cookie Was Removed
Visualforce Section Header Components Are Secure by Default

To prepare for two release updates, view blocked redirections and resources in an updated Setup page. Reduce emails about certificate expirations, and create certificates with a 3072-bit key length. And refresh Named Credentials access tokens based on non-standard HTTP status codes.

Allow Only Trusted Cross-Org Redirections (Release Update)
Adopt Updated Content Security Policy (CSP) Directives (Release Update)
Review and Resolve Blocked External Redirections
IdeaExchange Delivered: Limit Who Receives Notifications About Certificate Expiration
Control Which HTTP Status Codes Refresh Access Tokens for Named Credentials
Confirm Access to External Systems When Named Credentials Use the OAuth 2.0 Browser Flow
Create 3072-Bit Sized Certificates
Audit More Changes to Salesforce Sites and Visualforce Sites
Enjoy Faster Load Times for Cached Salesforce Site Pages
The BrowserId_sec Cookie Was Removed
Visualforce Section Header Components Are Secure by Default

Other Security Changes 

To protect your users and network, limit redirections to other Salesforce orgs. Add the specific Salesforce org URLs that you trust to the Trusted URLs for Redirects allowlist.
Help protect your org from cross-site scripting and other code injection attacks with updated Content Security Policy (CSP) directives. Review the impact and update your trusted URLs.
Reduce research and resolution time for allowing external redirections, including cross-org redirections.
Control who receives notifications about certificate expiration and include more details in notification emails.
Refresh Named Credentials access tokens based on non-standard HTTP status codes.
Confirm access to external systems when named credentials use OAuth 2.0 browser flow authentication.
Create self-signed or CA (Certificate Authority)-signed certificates with a 3072-bit key length for stronger security without performance limitations.
Track changes to more Salesforce Sites and Visualforce sites settings in Site History.
Update caching behavior for public Salesforce Site pages to improve page load times.
Remove the BrowserId_sec cookie, which serves the same purpose as the BrowserId cookie. 
Only commonly used, secure HTML elements are evaluated in the <apex:sectionHeader> component’s description attribute by default.
title: Security Changes for Salesforce Summer '24 Release
